1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,120
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:01,160 --> 00:00:02,320
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:17,400
Don't treat me too well,

4
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:18,320
or I'll get spoiled.

5
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,680
I'm going to Bang Saen this Friday

6
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:21,240
to draw for a school project.

7
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:22,640
With who?

8
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:24,040
They don't have a crush on you, right?

9
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,360
I don't know if others
have a crush on me,

10
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,600
but all I know is that

11
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:28,880
my heart is all yours.

12
00:00:29,490 --> 00:00:30,040
Qin!

13
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:30,960
Can we talk for a second?

14
00:00:32,119 --> 00:00:33,240
Are you already in a relationship?

15
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,760
I just want to have a nice chat with you.

16
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,520
You two were friends?

17
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:38,360
We weren't really

18
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:39,640
in the talking stage, either.

19
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:41,240
When he confessed how he felt about me...

20
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:43,160
Since then, we rarely talked.

21
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:44,760
Was I a mean person?

22
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:48,120
You were.

23
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,200
But I never thought of you as a friend.

24
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,000
We agreed

25
00:00:58,480 --> 00:00:59,680
we'd be each other's partner.

26
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:07,640
Mm.

27
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:22,400
You're still upset?

28
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:29,800
Yes.

29
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,960
We're in the talking stage.

30
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:38,920
Duang, just get to the point.

31
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,800
Don't sound so harsh.

32
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:47,400
I'm not being harsh.

33
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,039
You're overly possessive
and such a crybaby.

34
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,680
Take a shower with me tonight.

35
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,040
Huh?

36
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,560
What did you say just now?

37
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,360
Not going to say it twice.

38
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,360
It's on you if you didn't catch that.

39
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,140
Ow! Hey!

40
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,320
That hurt.

41
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,280
Pretending you didn't hear that?

42
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:28,600
Playing hard to get?

43
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,160
Hey...

44
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,960
Stop clinging to my leg.

45
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,400
I'll let you shower with me,

46
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,400
but don't get any funny ideas.

47
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,120
No physical contact.

48
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:51,560
Understood?

49
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:53,579
Understood!

50
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:58,640
Right.

51
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,320
There's one more thing I want to tell you.

52
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,000
Tiw never got to shower with me.

53
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:37,480
♫I'm not leaving soon, so bear with me♫

54
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:42,620
♫Wherever you are
is where I'll always be♫

55
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:46,520
♫Wherever you go,
I'll find you eventually♫

56
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,840
♫You may push me away, but I won't flee♫

57
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:51,880
♫Who would you love if it weren't me?♫

58
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:54,160
♫So, wanna make a deal, maybe?♫

59
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:56,560
♫Alright, alright, don't worry♫

60
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,840
♫Just date me first, take it easy♫

61
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:01,240
♫I'll be so cute you'll fall naturally♫

62
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,560
♫No matter what,
you'll always run into me♫

63
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,960
♫Okay, okay, let it be♫

64
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,280
♫I know you're also into me,♫

65
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:10,800
♫Don't you feel the same? I can see♫

66
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:17,079
♫I'll keep on flirting,
don't try to avoid me♫

67
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:21,880
♫'Cause I won't stop
till you fall for me♫

68
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:26,440
♫I'll keep on flirting,
I won't stop, I guarantee♫

69
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:32,880
♫I'll love you hard,
and once you say yes, I'll set you free♫

70
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:42,440
♫I'm the only one stuck in what's passed♫

71
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:48,040
♫Having no one to erase our shared blast♫

72
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:53,680
♫Lonely days for me while you're with him♫

73
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:58,680
♫My feelings, they never dim♫

74
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:02,710
♫The cold breeze arrives♫

75
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:06,080
So he's your boyfriend, correct?

76
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,360
What's that got to do with you?

77
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,480
Can you just give me a clear answer?

78
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,520
I'm trying to be nice here.

79
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,520
Duang is not just a friend. That's all.

80
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:42,920
Where are you going? Come here.

81
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,360
Take a seat.

82
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,159
Hold him.

83
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:49,960
What's wrong?

84
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:53,320
I'm sure it's about Qin, not his grades.

85
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,720
I'll bet 10 baht.

86
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,080
Mm.

87
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,240
It's about Qin.

88
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,280
No way.

89
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:02,320
Next time,
tell me the winning lottery number.

90
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:04,400
Shut it! I'm not a sacred entity.

91
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,280
Guys, listen to me first.

92
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,480
I met that guy.

93
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:09,640
Who?

94
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:11,520
It's the guy,

95
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,760
the one who gave Qin the teddy bear.

96
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,600
Oh.

97
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:15,400
Hold him.

98
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,600
Come.

99
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,480
Let me do a recap.

100
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,760
This bastard! Whoa!

101
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,320
Duang...

102
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:29,180
He came across Qin's post from years ago.

103
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:30,760
It was a photo of him with a friend,

104
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,280
aka

105
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,840
someone he used to flirt with.

106
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:34,740
Oh?

107
00:06:34,780 --> 00:06:35,720
That's why he became

108
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,840
a sad boy.

109
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,200
How are you doing, by the way?

110
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,680
Whoa, whoa.

111
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:43,880
Just sit.

112
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,800
Nothing much, really.

113
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,320
I met the guy yesterday.

114
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,320
Qin told me that they were friends.

115
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:53,640
Huh? So the teddy bear...

116
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,040
So that's all in the past, right?

117
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,240
Mm.

118
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:58,960
If so, then why are you looking all blue?

119
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,280
He said they were friends,

120
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,900
but he still keeps the teddy bear.

121
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:03,600
Huh?

122
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,760
Why didn't he throw it away?

123
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,600
Yeah.

124
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,960
Why don't you tell him to do so?

125
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,480
Do I have that power, though?

126
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,280
What?!

127
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,200
Of course, you do!

128
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,040
Aren't you in the talking stage with him?

129
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,960
Do you think
I've got the guts to tell him that?

130
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,300
If I tell him,
but he refuses to throw it away,

131
00:07:18,340 --> 00:07:19,880
I'd end up even worse than a lost puppy.

132
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:22,560
Well, you're already more than
a lost puppy.

133
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,560
Plus, it's not looking good for you.

134
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,520
I'm saying this
because I don't want you to risk it.

135
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:30,600
Come on. You're overthinking it.

136
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,700
- You won't know until you try, right?
- Mm.

137
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,480
It's okay.

138
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:36,210
Even if he stops loving you,

139
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,520
we still do, alright?

140
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,560
Jamie...

141
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,960
- Don't turn pink just now.
- I'll only take kisses from Qin.

142
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,960
My kisses are better than Qin's, you know?

143
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,640
Duang, my baby!

144
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,640
I already got you yuzu ramen with chashu.

145
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,880
No green onions,

146
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,560
extra chashu, and extra noodles.

147
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,880
Anything else you'd like to order?

148
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,640
You remember I don't like green onions?

149
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:19,040
Of course, why wouldn't I?

150
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:26,640
Oh?

151
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:28,480
You're blushing, aren't you?

152
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:32,000
Nobody else is like you.

153
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,120
You never blush.

154
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:36,000
I do,

155
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,600
but I don't let it out of my heart.

156
00:08:38,299 --> 00:08:39,000
Gosh.

157
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:41,080
I don't think
it's ever been kept in there.

158
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,760
Your skin is too thick.

159
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:47,680
Thick but soft, alright?

160
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:49,200
Do you want to try it?

161
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,180
Place your order already. I'm starving.

162
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,080
Two sets, please.

163
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:14,560
Oh.

164
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,600
I saw the post on Instagram.

165
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,560
The music students are hosting
a jazz showcase, right?

166
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,680
Mm.

167
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,600
It's for a studio class.

168
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,840
Whoa!

169
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,160
Really?

170
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,360
Will you be onstage, too?

171
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,160
I have to,

172
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,400
but my friends want me to be the vocalist.

173
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,320
I don't want to.

174
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:35,640
Why not?

175
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,600
You're extremely talented.

176
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,640
You sing and play guitar very well.

177
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,520
I'm not that great.

178
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,440
You are!

179
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:46,040
I still remember the day
we were onstage.

180
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,320
You were the superstar back there.

181
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:49,560
You were killing it!

182
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,480
Not really.

183
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,600
I almost couldn't finish the song

184
00:09:54,780 --> 00:09:55,960
without you by my side.

185
00:09:58,540 --> 00:10:00,540
You don't want to do it
because I'm not there with you?

186
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,020
How about this?

187
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,400
I'll be there right in front of you
wherever you go.

188
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:17,840
Just tell me,

189
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,360
and I'll be there.

190
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,080
Do you think

191
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:26,120
I sound emotionless when I sing?

192
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:30,560
Don't blame me for this,

193
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,440
but, for me,

194
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,960
just seeing you stand there
already moves me.

195
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:38,060
But...

196
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,520
I'm not sure
if I can give you an unbiased answer

197
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,940
to what you're looking for.

198
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:45,160
Forget it.

199
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,920
But your goal is to be a singer, isn't it?

200
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,000
I don't know.

201
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,200
I know that you do.

202
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,200
Honestly,

203
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,460
I want you to trust me
more than anybody else,

204
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,080
but you're stubborn.

205
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,040
You won't listen to what people say.

206
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,120
I think...

207
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,880
What's good for you

208
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,800
is to trust yourself.

209
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,700
Here's a trick I'd like to add.

210
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:38,000
While we were onstage,

211
00:11:38,820 --> 00:11:40,120
I was terrified, you know?

212
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,400
But I put all of my fears onto you.

213
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,360
And I want you to do the same.

214
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,680
Although this time,

215
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:59,320
I might not get to go onstage with you,

216
00:12:00,260 --> 00:12:01,880
I'll be there in the crowd.

217
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,880
I'll be in the very front row,

218
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:07,560
the very same spot where I fell for you.

219
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,520
Put all your worries and fears on me.

220
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:16,360
I'll take care of them myself.

221
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,220
Are you free tonight?

222
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:27,440
Let's party at the same old bar.

223
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,160
Hey.

224
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,960
Jamie asked if I wanted to drink.

225
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,820
Mm. You can go.

226
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:34,200
Wanna go there together?

227
00:12:37,980 --> 00:12:38,980
So?

228
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,520
Even in this dim light,

229
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,960
you still look as lovely as ever.

230
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,840
Duang, come on now.

231
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,440
I ordered deep-fried chicken tendons.

232
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,400
If they're finished, I'll order more.

233
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,920
I love you so much, Qin.

234
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:10,360
You can't say
that kind of stuff here, alright?

235
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,440
You know whose man he is?

236
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,600
He's mine alone!

237
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,480
Well, I want the chicken tendons...

238
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,120
Whatever.

239
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,200
The girl behind us is fire.

240
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:37,960
Who?

241
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,340
- Hey!
- That table.

242
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:43,880
What?

243
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,800
What is it?

244
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,560
Qin.

245
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:52,920
What brings you here?

246
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,320
Hi, guys.

247
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,000
How about a toast?

248
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,260
Cheers.

249
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:09,080
A toast.

250
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:12,480
Tonight, aside from him,

251
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,960
nobody else has asked you to toast, right?

252
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,480
Can I borrow Qin for a bit?

253
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,280
Hey, come with us.

254
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,320
The rest of us really want to meet you.

255
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:36,760
Come on, this way.

256
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:37,960
I'll be back shortly.

257
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:41,000
Right this way.

258
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,640
This way.

259
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:44,080
Whoa! He came!

260
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,240
Oh.

261
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,880
Whoa, you came? Come take a seat.

262
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:47,880
I'm not here to borrow him.

263
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:49,840
I'm here to take him back.

264
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:50,800
Whoa.

265
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,960
Think you're cool?

266
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,120
Sit down!

267
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,640
The guy's cheeky, alright?

268
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:05,200
Take him back? Seriously?

269
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,440
This is upsetting.

270
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,200
I trust Qin,

271
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,700
but not that bastard.

272
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:17,160
Yeah, I don't trust him either.

273
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,640
He even raised an eyebrow at me.

274
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:23,280
It's hard to believe that
all of us managed to gather here.

275
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,720
I want to play a game.
Care to join?

276
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:25,680
- Yeah.
- Sure.

277
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,920
- Bring it on.
- Let's play.

278
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:29,480
I watched a series called...
What's it called again?

279
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:31,640
It's called 'Bet...'

280
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:32,800
Whatever.

281
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,440
The game's called "Heart Rate."

282
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:36,400
Clear the table for me.

283
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,320
- Alright, let's go.
- What the hell is "Heart Rate"?

284
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,520
- Alright. Clear the table.
- What kind of game is this?

285
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:43,320
Right.

286
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,380
First.

287
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,880
Jay and Ya, give me your smart watch.

288
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:49,020
Each of you, give yours to me.

289
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:50,880
What the hell?

290
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,560
Can't afford a smart watch?

291
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,840
Damn it. These are required for the game.

292
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:55,520
Alright.

293
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,720
The rules are simple.

294
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,320
Answer a question,
and if your heart rate goes above 100 bpm,

295
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,040
bottoms up.

296
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,400
- Shit!
- Yo!

297
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:05,520
- Understood?
- Qin, are you playing?

298
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:06,840
- Interesting.
- No.

299
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,920
- What? You're not playing?
- Qin!

300
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,720
We only get to hang out once in a while.

301
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:11,620
- Yeah.
- Play the game, please.

302
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:12,560
Please! Please!

303
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,600
- Come on.
- Don't chicken out.

304
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:15,000
Okay. Let me demonstrate the game.

305
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,840
Kie, play with me.

306
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,160
- Me?
- Yes, you.

307
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:22,880
- Alright. Bring it on!
- Let's see.

308
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,040
Let's play Rock, Paper, and Scissors.

309
00:16:24,260 --> 00:16:25,160
The winner goes first.

310
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,000
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

311
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,420
- I win!
- You're first.

312
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,440
Alright.

313
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:33,900
- Cho.
- Yes?

314
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:37,240
When you got spanked in front of everyone
at the morning assembly,

315
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:38,840
you were embarrassed, right?

316
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,480
You laughed so fucking loud, Jay.

317
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,200
Ha, it's below 100 bpm, stupid.

318
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,540
My turn.

319
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:53,720
Dao...

320
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:57,400
Oh, Dao...

321
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,920
You said that you dumped her,

322
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,520
but it was actually
the other way around, no?

323
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:01,840
What?!

324
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:04,160
- Sheesh!
- What's the truth?

325
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,359
- Explain yourself.
- Gosh.

326
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:06,760
What's the truth?

327
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,240
It's 110 bpm. You lost, stupid!

328
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,160
- Bottoms up!
- Bottoms up!

329
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:15,800
Chug! Chug! Chug!

330
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:21,060
Alright. Who's next?

331
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,000
You?

332
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:24,319
I'm out. I'm wasted. Play without me.

333
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:26,359
Jay, you can't play this game.
You're full of secrets.

334
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,119
- Whoa!
- Go for it.

335
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:29,560
I'll play.

336
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,360
- Who's he playing with?
- But under one condition.

337
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,640
I'm playing with Qin.

338
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,520
Damn.

339
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:39,160
Sheesh.

340
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:40,480
What?

341
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,680
Are you afraid you'll lose?

342
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:44,800
Or afraid you'll give in to your feelings?

343
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,520
Damn!

344
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:48,560
He's taunting him.

345
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,160
If you're not up for this game,

346
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:51,560
it's okay.

347
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:53,920
Everyone will know that

348
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,000
you're still longing for me.

349
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,440
- Damn!
- Yo!

350
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,640
For real?

351
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,800
He's so damn full of himself.

352
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:05,760
He's giving Qin no fucking choice.

353
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:10,920
- I'm in.
- Here we go!

354
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,640
- Whoa!
- That's the spirit!

355
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:14,840
- This is a fun night.
- What a match this is.

356
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,760
Alright. Make it nice and tight.

357
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,600
You refused to accept my love

358
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:31,520
because you have commitment issues, no?

359
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,200
Shit...

360
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,920
- Shit...
- This first question is a tough one.

361
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:40,720
I guess not.

362
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,920
You intentionally ghosted me, didn't you?

363
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:48,480
Whoa!

364
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,360
I'm preparing a shot just for you.

365
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,600
It's going up! Damn!

366
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,800
The teddy I gave you...

367
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,520
You still hold onto it, don't you?

368
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:05,680
- What a question?!
- Damn!

369
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,280
- Sheesh!
- Response?

370
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:10,160
An old flame is being rekindled!

371
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,520
It's waiting to be reignited!

372
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,800
♫The one who came after♫

373
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:15,680
- What?
- Hey, that's not it.

374
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,440
You came back for me now

375
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:34,840
because it'd be a shame to lose me, right?

376
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:37,000
- Whoa.
- Sheesh.

377
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:38,960
- Damn!
- It'd be a shame.

378
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:39,760
Close...

379
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,360
- It's getting close.
- Do you want a shot now?

380
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:43,080
- Whoa! Whoa!
- It's so close!

381
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,500
- It's so close, Tiw!
- 99 bpm?! Damn!

382
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,600
- Oh? Tiw?
- It's hitting 100 bpm.

383
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,720
You're going to lose!

384
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,480
You asked me that

385
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:55,600
because you're still into me, right?

386
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:57,200
- Ah!
- Shit?!

387
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,680
- What's it going to be?
- Straight to the point.

388
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,080
- Oh? It's rising.
- Not playing around.

389
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:01,760
Oh? Here we go!

390
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,440
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

391
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:24,600
- Oh, dear!
- Here we go!

392
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:27,160
The tables have turned!

393
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:35,480
Chug! Chug! Chug!

394
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:38,040
Chug...

395
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,720
- Oh...
- Chug...

396
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:41,160
Hey.

397
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,620
Be honest.

398
00:20:42,660 --> 00:20:45,120
Do you two still feel the same way?

399
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:47,080
- I'm kidding.
- The game's fucking over, right?

400
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:55,840
Where are you going?

401
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,600
Let's talk outside.

402
00:20:58,580 --> 00:20:59,720
We've got nothing to talk about.

403
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:01,920
We can talk at your table.

404
00:21:07,060 --> 00:21:08,000
Why cause trouble?

405
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:08,880
What?

406
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,760
Can't I be at your table?

407
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:20,400
Oh...

408
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:22,280
Where is he taking Qin to?

409
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,960
Duang, this is the moment.

410
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,280
Go after them.

411
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:26,080
Hey.

412
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:27,840
I don't think this is the time.

413
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:29,280
Let them talk.

414
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:31,200
Let Duang clear things up later.

415
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:34,480
I don't think Qin is an irrational person.
Think about it.

416
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,080
Pae...

417
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:38,080
He can't give up.

418
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,300
If they reconcile,

419
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,920
then who is Duang in this relationship?

420
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,740
- I agree with him, though.
- Huh?

421
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:45,920
I told you.

422
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,680
There are two conditions for me
to stop chasing Qin's heart.

423
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:51,400
If he wants to get back
with the owner of the teddy,

424
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,440
then I'm out of the game, right?

425
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:58,200
Damn it.
You're called a lover boy for a reason.

426
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,440
Is this really your call?

427
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:03,440
Duang, get a grip.

428
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,520
Who are you?

429
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:05,640
What are you saying?

430
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:08,120
Who the hell are you?
I don't know who this is.

431
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,940
Duang that I know

432
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:11,760
always fights till the end.

433
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:13,640
Hey.

434
00:22:13,980 --> 00:22:14,960
Listen to me.

435
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:19,000
If you don't want to be a sad puppy
like Pae said,

436
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,480
then go after Qin.

437
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:23,280
Wait!

438
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:25,920
If he's going to punch you,
scream as loud as you can, okay?

439
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:27,120
We'll be there.

440
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,200
Okay!

441
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:33,720
Is he going to be fine?

442
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,520
We're not going to go after him?

443
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,120
I think Qin can handle this.

444
00:22:38,340 --> 00:22:40,280
Let Duang hear it from Qin's mouth.

445
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,280
My heart was racing
because of someone else, not you.

446
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,360
You can now explain how you feel?

447
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:46,920
You said nothing back then.

448
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:49,040
This is why nobody wants to stay with you.

449
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:49,760
Tiw.

450
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,200
You've crossed the fucking line.

451
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,760
I know you more than anyone else.

452
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,520
That's why I have the guts to say this.

453
00:22:57,420 --> 00:22:58,620
Then you probably knew

454
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,160
I was starting to fall for you back then.

455
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:06,380
I once loved you, Tiw.

456
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,000
I just want to know...

457
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:12,680
what I did wrong
when I was trying to take things slowly.

458
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:46,040
Hey, wait.

459
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:48,240
Where's Tiw?

460
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,000
I don't know.

461
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:53,980
You two are in the talking stage, aren't you?

462
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:56,400
Why don't you ask him yourself?

463
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,080
I'm going back to practice now.

464
00:24:06,460 --> 00:24:07,920
I never fucking understood it.

465
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:12,000
When you wanted me,
you gave it your all.

466
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,480
But when I tried to love you back...

467
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:17,400
Why did you give up on me?

468
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:18,720
Why did you disappear?

469
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:21,000
- Why did you...
- Not everyone can wait for you, Qin.

470
00:24:21,540 --> 00:24:23,720
It's true I started at a hundred,

471
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:25,920
but no one can stay at a hundred forever.

472
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:28,520
People lose hope too, you know.

473
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:31,340
It felt like trying to fill
a bottomless hole with love.

474
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:32,880
And?

475
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,960
How long do I still have to wait?

476
00:24:35,780 --> 00:24:37,860
Have you ever tried
seeing things from my perspective?

477
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:39,920
If you don't love me anymore,
just tell me.

478
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:41,480
Why did you go and find someone else?

479
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:46,360
Come back here!

480
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,920
Where's Tiw?

481
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:57,400
No clue.

482
00:24:58,500 --> 00:24:59,120
What?

483
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,840
You two are usually glued to each other,
aren't you?

484
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,160
Yeah.

485
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:04,920
I'm heading home now.

486
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,400
Hey, Tiw. Where are you going?

487
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,760
I'm busy.

488
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,440
I'm seeing Sea.

489
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:18,360
Who's that?

490
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,260
You'll find out soon.

491
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:22,440
See you.

492
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,280
Tiw.

493
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,620
I heard you're dating someone new?

494
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:33,960
Why the hell did you do this to Qin?

495
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:36,280
What did I do?

496
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,560
There's nothing going on
between him and me.

497
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:40,520
What do you mean by that?

498
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,960
You two are in...

499
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,320
the talking stage, aren't you?

500
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:47,360
You call this the talking stage?

501
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,800
It's very one-sided.

502
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,680
That's not true.

503
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:53,840
How is that not true?

504
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:55,880
I asked him about us,

505
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:57,720
but he wouldn't say a word.

506
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,840
So what else do you want me to do?

507
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:02,200
You have no idea how torturous it's been,

508
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:03,560
being in such a one-sided relationship.

509
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:06,000
It felt like trying to fill
a bottomless hole with love.

510
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:08,040
No one knows if it'll ever be filled.

511
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,040
I'm not staying.

512
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:15,240
Then why don't you tell Qin?

513
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,120
You want me to do that?

514
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:19,320
What good would that do?

515
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:21,720
Qin won't change himself for anyone.

516
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,400
That hurt like hell back then, you know?

517
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:28,640
I wish I could cry like everyone else,

518
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:30,120
but I couldn't.

519
00:26:30,960 --> 00:26:33,160
Being heartbroken
and unable to cry hurt so much.

520
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:35,560
But that's okay.

521
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:38,800
I was good on my own.

522
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,680
I just had to get back
to doing things like I used to,

523
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:42,840
without you.

524
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,120
It's too late to fix anything now, Qin.

525
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:46,920
I didn't realize it

526
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,680
until I was dating someone else.

527
00:26:49,470 --> 00:26:51,120
- What did you realize?
- I regretted it.

528
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,680
I want to ask you one question.

529
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:58,680
Just one question.

530
00:27:00,340 --> 00:27:01,560
All you have to do is tell me

531
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:04,600
you still feel the same.

532
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,200
And that'll be it.

533
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:07,720
Tiw...

534
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:08,840
How about we start dating?

535
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:08,920
Wait, Qin.

536
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,040
- Let go of me.
- We're not done here.

537
00:28:12,280 --> 00:28:13,120
Where are you going?

538
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:18,280
We weren't done last time
because you fucking ran away.

539
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,040
What do you want from me now?

540
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,600
I'm not running away this time.

541
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:25,920
Duang! Duang!

542
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:27,020
Duang...

543
00:28:30,060 --> 00:28:31,160
Watch the table for me.

544
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:32,080
Right...

545
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,800
What the hell?

546
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,160
Let's settle this here,

547
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,120
so you can get out of my life.

548
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:42,600
Sure.

549
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:43,960
Let's do this.

550
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:45,920
I'm not someone you can just break up with

551
